items.title: WATCH: "Euphoria" for Olympians at marathon in Pyongyang

fields.Description: Olympic snowboarder Aimee Fuller reacts after completing the race in the Democractic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK). items.title: Olympic mindset helped Michael Johnson get "back to normal" after stroke

fields.Description: The four-time Olympic champion says the "Olympic mindset" was a key part of the recovery from a stroke he suffered in August 2018. Johnson also hopes to raise awareness and inspire others in similar circumstances to get back their "quality of life".
fields.MetaTitle: Olympic mindset key to Johnson recovery
fields.MetaDescription: USA sprint star Michael Johnson is "back to normal" after suffering a stroke. The "Olympic mindset" was key in the four-time gold medallists recovery.

items.title: Against the odds: Meet the USA artistic swim team targeting Tokyo 2020

fields.Description: What does it take to break 12 years of disappointment? Olympic Channel got an exclusive invite to go behind the scenes with the U.S. artistic swimming team to find out. This is the story of how a group of young hopefuls, a star choreographer, a four-time Olympic medal winning coach, and a group of mum's are synchronising together with the Tokyo 2020 Games as a goal.
fields.MetaTitle: The USA artistic swimmers aiming at 2020
fields.MetaDescription: They missed London 2012 and Rio 2016, but the USA artistic swim team  and their four-time Olympic medal winning coach Andrea Fuentes are pushing on.

items.title: News of the Week with Ash Tulloch (5th April 2019)

fields.Description: How a choreography created by a robot dance specialist could help the USA break an unwanted streak, why Paula Radcliffe is putting her Olympic disappointments to good use, and which Japanese snowboarder should you be watching out for in skateboarding at Tokyo 2020.
fields.MetaTitle: News of the Week with Ash (5 April 2019)
fields.MetaDescription: Robot dance specialist 'Madd Chadd' is helping the USA try to break an unwanted streak, plus more athletes aiming for Tokyo 2020 in our round-up.

items.title: John John Florence ready to prove doubters wrong

fields.Description: There is a lot at stake in 2019 before surfing makes its Olympic debut at Tokyo 2020. The two-time world champion has been sidelined since June of last year when he suffered a knee injury while surfing in Bali. As a new WSL season starts, Florence wants to show he can compete at top-level again.
fields.MetaTitle: John John Florence is back
fields.MetaDescription: The American is making his comeback ready to show the world he still has what it takes.
